records.addlTxt:
Statements made by the State, Defense Counsel, and Defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1:
The Court sentenced the defendant to 8 MONTHS in the House of Correction, CONCURRENT to Count 2, with credit for 4 days time served. The Court granted Huber privileges for work.  Court allows for good time credit. 

AS TO COUNT 2:
The Court sentenced the defendant to 8 MONTHS in the House of Correction, CONCURRENT to Count 1, with credit for 4 days time served. The Court granted Huber privileges for work.  Court allows for good time credit. 

AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 2:
The Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 2 YEARS. 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION: 
- AODA assessment and cooperate with any recommended treatment.
- Absolute sobriety.
- Random urine screens and breathalyzers. 
- Provide DNA sample.
- No use or possession of alcohol or illegal drugs.
- Maintain employment.
- No new law violations arising to the level of probable cause
- Follow all rules of supervision and follow through with any other treatment deemed necessary by the department. 
- NO CONTACT with victim SH or residing location: 2843 N. 26th St., Milwaukee, WI

Court set restitution at $0.00.  Court ordered the defendant to pay all mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges (including DNA) by the end of supervision.  Court waived all non-mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges.  Failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment.  Bail on deposit shall be applied.  Any remaining amount shall be returned to poster.  

20 day appeal rights given.

Defendant Leequinace Giovann Turner in court.  Attorney Connor Romenesko in court for Leequinace Giovann Turner.  Attorney James C Griffin in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in court for plea/sentencing.  State filed Amended Information.  Defense acknowledges receipt of Amended Information, waives formal reading, and temporarily pleads not guilty on behalf of Mr. Turner.

Parties have reached an agreement.  Plea negotiations set forth on the record and agreed upon by the parties.  Defendant sworn. 

AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 2:
Defendant changes pleas to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to pleas, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Defendant further advised that if not a US citizen, deportation is possible. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, Addendum, and Elements/Jury Instructions received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's pleas.  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.
